        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3950837367" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8193706736316758627">I was surprised to find my 11 year old daughter reading this. I suppose I shouldnâ€™t have been so surprised. I had bought it for her, but as one of a large stack I had brought home for her to choose from. She chose this one first. Afterwards, when it was my turn to read it in one breathless go, she was not surprised that I loved it. What a lyrical voyage through the hard things we wish our kids will never experience, full of the wisdom and hope and resilience we hope theyâ€™ll find in themselves wh</span>
  <span id="freeText8193706736316758627" style="display:none">I was surprised to find my 11 year old daughter reading this. I suppose I shouldnâ€™t have been so surprised. I had bought it for her, but as one of a large stack I had brought home for her to choose from. She chose this one first. Afterwards, when it was my turn to read it in one breathless go, she was not surprised that I loved it. What a lyrical voyage through the hard things we wish our kids will never experience, full of the wisdom and hope and resilience we hope theyâ€™ll find in themselves when they do. I am tempted to write a note, slip it into the pages of this book before I place it on our shelves for her to discover again, later. It definitely has that fairytale quality of offering different insights for different times of society, different ages of life chapters. It was a beautiful read to share with my daughter. Thankyou, Ms. Hoffman. </span>
