  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2364808176" />
    <a title="Ken Hulse" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28733698-ken-hulse"><img alt="Ken Hulse" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2364808176?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ken Hulse" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ken Hulse" href="/user/show/28733698-ken-hulse">Ken Hulse</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/13453822-green-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2364808176" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3266021692273431552">There are all kind of writers who write about all sorts of situations. Some are really good, some just are too predictable with too much filler. One never knows what one is going to get despite sometimes glowing reviews.<br/><br/>Alice Hoffman is not just good she is amazing. When she writes she takes you on journey about life that is filled with magical writing and beautiful turns of phrase. This book is essentially a September 11 type of catastrophe with a dystopian consequence. The repairing the fabric</span>
  <span id="freeText3266021692273431552" style="display:none">There are all kind of writers who write about all sorts of situations. Some are really good, some just are too predictable with too much filler. One never knows what one is going to get despite sometimes glowing reviews.<br /><br />Alice Hoffman is not just good she is amazing. When she writes she takes you on journey about life that is filled with magical writing and beautiful turns of phrase. This book is essentially a September 11 type of catastrophe with a dystopian consequence. The repairing the fabric of society and coming to terms with life is the basic premise but the writing is just the best. I read her Blackbird House book and loved it. Thus I tried this one. In my view you can always expect good writing from her.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3266021692273431552" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


